Mogadishu - A suicide car bomber killed at least eight people in Somalia's capital Mogadishu, police said on Sunday. At least 10 others were wounded when the bomb exploded in front of a building housing government officials in Hawlwadaag district on Sunday morning, police officer Ali Hassan Kulmiye told dpa. Most victims were civilians, according to Kulmiye. Islamist terrorist group al-Shabaab claimed responsibility for the attack via pro-insurgent radio station Andalus. The group is affiliated with the international al-Qaeda terrorist network and launches regular attacks within the volatile East African nation. * Receive IOL's top stories via Whatsapp by sending your name to 0745573535. dpa